967
00:58:04.440 --> 00:58:07.558
He thinks you're talking a load of shit.
Swings and roundabouts, isn't it?

968
00:58:07.880 --> 00:58:09.075
CARTWRIGHT: Pain in the arse.

969
00:58:09.320 --> 00:58:11.277
-Did you find anything?
-Yeah.

970
00:58:11.360 --> 00:58:13.112
I was extremely shocked
when I looked at my watch

971
00:58:13.200 --> 00:58:14.554
and discovered that I should be in the pub.

972
00:58:14.640 --> 00:58:16.836
Did you go to his house?
Did you read his articles?

973
00:58:16.920 --> 00:58:20.231
If you wanna wade through every copy of
the Sandford bloody Citizen, be our guest.

974
00:58:20.320 --> 00:58:22.152
It's your job, isn't it? Detect!

975
00:58:22.240 --> 00:58:26.313
This ain't the city, Mr Angel.
Not everyone's a murdering psychopath.

976
00:58:26.480 --> 00:58:29.757
It's high time you realised that.
You and your monkey.

977
00:58:32.960 --> 00:58:34.837
Did he mean me or that?

978
00:58:36.440 --> 00:58:38.556
Oh, maybe we should go home.

979
00:58:38.760 --> 00:58:41.718
-What do you mean?
-Well, there's nothing going on, is there?

980
00:58:41.800 --> 00:58:43.359
Have you listened to anything that I've said?

981
00:58:43.440 --> 00:58:44.510
What do you mean?

982
00:58:44.600 --> 00:58:46.079
Is anything I've told you
in the last two weeks

983
00:58:46.160 --> 00:58:48.117
-sunk into that thick skull of yours?
-Yeah.

984
00:58:48.200 --> 00:58:49.838
Has it? Like what?

985
00:58:50.360 --> 00:58:52.192
You said I could be
an amazing policeman-officer.

986
00:58:52.280 --> 00:58:54.590
There's always something going on, Danny.

987
00:58:54.680 --> 00:58:58.150
And you won't be an amazing police officer
until you understand that.

988
00:58:58.240 --> 00:59:00.516
Well, I remembered something else
you said and all.

989
00:59:00.600 --> 00:59:02.159
-Oh, did you now?
-Yeah.

990
00:59:02.240 --> 00:59:04.436
You don't know how to switch off!

991
00:59:12.720 --> 00:59:17.715


992
00:59:37.240 --> 00:59:38.639
Well, if you wanna wade through every copy

993
00:59:38.720 --> 00:59:40.916
of the Sandford bloody Citizen,
be our guest.

994
01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:19.469
-Morning, Constable.
-All right?

995
01:00:20.760 --> 01:00:22.592
Thanks for the monkey.

996
01:00:23.400 --> 01:00:25.835
-Yours, isn't it?
-I won it for you.

997
01:00:29.320 --> 01:00:31.197
Danny, I think I'm on to something.

998
01:00:31.280 --> 01:00:32.395
-Are you?
-Yes.

999
01:00:32.480 --> 01:00:36.633
And I think with a little deliberation
we can figure out what links these deaths.

1000
01:00:37.080 --> 01:00:40.357
-We?
-Come on, partner. Let's go to work.

1001
01:00:41.440 --> 01:00:43.272
Oh, oh, Sergeant Angel?

1002
01:00:43.360 --> 01:00:47.797
-Someone from London called for you.
-Tell them I'll call them back.

1003
01:00:48.600 --> 01:00:49.670
-Tim Messenger.
-Go.

1004
01:00:49.760 --> 01:00:51.512
Editor and journalist
at The Sandford Citizen.

1005
01:00:51.600 --> 01:00:52.829
-Fondness for puns.
-Go on.

1006
01:00:52.920 --> 01:00:53.990
-Terrible speller.
-Oh, yeah?

1007
01:00:54.080 --> 01:00:55.957
Nevertheless had uncovered
important information about...

1008
01:00:56.040 --> 01:00:57.713
-George Merchant.
-Self-made millionaire.

1009
01:00:57.800 --> 01:00:59.916
Fancied himself as a property developer.

1010
01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:02.640
-Said he had big plans for Sandford.
-Pissed on the floor in The Crown.

1011
01:01:02.720 --> 01:01:04.791
But more importantly,
was a good friend and client of...

1012
01:01:04.880 --> 01:01:06.553
-Martin Blower.
-Respected solicitor.

1013
01:01:06.640 --> 01:01:08.790
-Affirmatron.
-Leading light of the local drama society.

1014
01:01:08.880 --> 01:01:10.234
-Bad actor.
-Undoubtedly.

1015
01:01:10.320 --> 01:01:11.799
-Bad driver.
-Not necessarily.

1016
01:01:11.880 --> 01:01:13.473
-Cheated on his missus.
-Most certainly.

1017
01:01:13.560 --> 01:01:15.437
-And we both know who with.
-Eve Draper.

1018
01:01:15.520 --> 01:01:18.239
-Blower's leading lady. Distinctive laugh.
-True.

1019
01:01:18.320 --> 01:01:19.674
-Favoured older men.
-Fingered.

1020
01:01:19.760 --> 01:01:20.955
-Worked at?
-Council.

1021
01:01:21.040 --> 01:01:23.634
-More specifically?
-Department of Planning and Development.

1022
01:01:23.720 --> 01:01:25.279
Where George Merchant secured permission

1023
01:01:25.360 --> 01:01:27.636
to build his dubious mansion
on Norris Avenue.

1024
01:01:27.720 --> 01:01:28.790
So...

1025
01:01:28.880 --> 01:01:32.794
Maybe they were all accidents.
People have accidents every day.

1026
01:01:32.880 --> 01:01:33.995
(MOCKING)

1027
01:01:34.080 --> 01:01:36.469
-What are you two up to?
-Nothing.

1028
01:01:36.560 --> 01:01:37.630
Well, look sharp.

1029
01:01:37.720 --> 01:01:40.360
-There's been reports of a fire in the station.
-What?

1030
01:01:40.440 --> 01:01:43.956
Happy birthday to you

1031
01:01:44.040 --> 01:01:48.079
Happy birthday to you

1032
01:01:48.160 --> 01:01:51.676
-Danny, why didn't you say something?
-We were working, weren't we?

1033
01:01:53.960 --> 01:01:56.918
-Hey, where are you going?
-Personal errand.

1034
01:01:57.600 --> 01:01:59.193
(SIREN BLARING)

1035
01:02:03.440 --> 01:02:04.794
Hello, Miss Tiller.

1036
01:02:04.880 --> 01:02:07.474
I was wondering,
do you have any Japanese Peace Lilies?

1037
01:02:07.560 --> 01:02:08.914
Of course.

1038
01:02:09.640 --> 01:02:11.995
I was just about to pop off, actually.

1039
01:02:12.800 --> 01:02:14.996
I can never find my scissors.

1040
01:02:15.240 --> 01:02:19.029
-Is this for someone special?
-Yes. Yes, it is.

1041
01:02:21.360 --> 01:02:25.797
-Are you going somewhere, Miss Tiller?
-Yes. I'm moving away.

1042
01:02:26.880 --> 01:02:29.918
And why the move,
if you don't mind me asking?

1043
01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:34.631
-Well, just between you and I...
-Yes?

1044
01:02:34.840 --> 01:02:37.639
-You know that fella who blew up?
-George Merchant.

1045
01:02:37.720 --> 01:02:40.758
Well, George Merchant, God rest him,
wanted to buy this land,

1046
01:02:40.840 --> 01:02:44.276
so he sends round his legal fella,
Martin Blower, God rest him,

1047
01:02:44.360 --> 01:02:46.397
and I thought I might take them up on it.

1048
01:02:46.480 --> 01:02:50.030
I haven't really got that much family
round here, save for Cousin Sissy.

1049
01:02:50.120 --> 01:02:53.431
So I thought I might take them up
on the offer and move to Buford Abbey.

1050
01:02:53.520 --> 01:02:55.431
Would you like a card with this?

1051
01:02:55.600 --> 01:02:57.796
No, sorry, you were talking about the offer?

1052
01:02:57.880 --> 01:03:00.952
Well, it turns out that Martin Blower,
God rest him,

1053
01:03:01.040 --> 01:03:03.111
knew where the new bypass road is going

1054
01:03:03.200 --> 01:03:06.158
because he was knocking off Eve Draper
from the council, God rest her,

1055
01:03:06.240 --> 01:03:09.790
and then that reporter, God rest him,
finds out about the route

1056
01:03:09.880 --> 01:03:11.917
and tells me this land's very valuable.

1057
01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:15.914
Ten times what George Merchant and
Martin Blower, God rest them, offered me.

1058
01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:18.879
So, with them having passed on,
I decided to sell it on myself

1059
01:03:18.960 --> 01:03:21.634
to some folks from the city
that Martin, George and Eve,

1060
01:03:21.720 --> 01:03:23.677
God rest the lot of them,
had been talking to.

1061
01:03:23.760 --> 01:03:26.479
Apparently, they want to build
a big shopping centre or something.

1062
01:03:26.560 --> 01:03:29.234
Of course, Cousin Sissy won't be
too happy about that,

1063
01:03:29.320 --> 01:03:31.311
but as far as I'm concerned,
Cousin Sissy can go and fuck...

1064
01:03:31.400 --> 01:03:33.914
Would you just excuse me,
for just one second?

1065
01:03:48.520 --> 01:03:49.669
Stop!

1066
01:03:50.520 --> 01:03:52.079
In the name of the law!

1067
01:04:47.880 --> 01:04:49.791
Hang about, hang about.

1068
01:04:50.600 --> 01:04:52.796
You're saying this wasn't an accident?

1069
01:04:54.080 --> 01:04:56.037
Leslie Tiller was fucking murdered!

1070
01:04:56.120 --> 01:04:57.519
-What, just like Tim Messenger?
-Yes!

1071
01:04:57.600 --> 01:04:58.715
-And George Merchant?
-Yes!

1072
01:04:58.800 --> 01:04:59.995
-And Eve Draper?
-Yes!

1073
01:05:00.080 --> 01:05:01.639
-And Martin Blower?
-No, actually.

1074
01:05:01.720 --> 01:05:03.518
-Really?
-'Course he fucking was!

1075
01:05:03.600 --> 01:05:05.432
Thank you, Danny.

1076
01:05:05.520 --> 01:05:08.717
Oh, murder, murder, murder.
Change the fucking record.

1077
01:05:09.280 --> 01:05:10.395
Thank you, Andy.

1078
01:05:10.480 --> 01:05:14.553
Come on, Sergeant, you've gotta accept
it was just another nasty accident.

1079
01:05:14.640 --> 01:05:15.675
What are you suggesting?

1080
01:05:15.760 --> 01:05:18.149
That Leslie Tiller tripped
and fell on her own shears?

1081
01:05:18.240 --> 01:05:20.595
Ben Fletcher fell
on his pitchfork the other week.

1082
01:05:20.680 --> 01:05:23.991
Yeah, accidents happen all the time.
What makes you think it was murder?

1083
01:05:24.080 --> 01:05:26.913
-Because I was there!
-There's a point.

1084
01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:28.320
Why were you there?

1085
01:05:28.400 --> 01:05:32.473
I was buying Constable Butterman
a Japanese Peace Lily for his birthday.

1086
01:05:32.560 --> 01:05:35.029
What absolute horseshit.

1087
01:05:35.120 --> 01:05:38.909
I chased a suspect from the scene.
Innocent people don't run!

1088
01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:41.958
Here, maybe it was our old friend,
the cactus thief.

1089
01:05:42.040 --> 01:05:44.634
Oh, yeah, he was a prickly customer,
weren't he?

1090
01:05:45.440 --> 01:05:48.034
Am I going completely mad?

1091
01:05:50.080 --> 01:05:51.673
Maybe you are.

1092
01:05:53.520 --> 01:05:56.160
Maybe you did it.

1093
01:05:56.240 --> 01:05:59.437
Yeah, seeing as how you're such
a big fan of murder.

1094
01:05:59.520 --> 01:06:00.874
-What the...
-Sergeant Angel?

1095
01:06:00.960 --> 01:06:03.349
Yes! Sir.

1096
01:06:05.840 --> 01:06:08.593
Nicholas, Nicholas, Nicholas.

1097
01:06:08.680 --> 01:06:11.149
What am I going to do with you?

1098
01:06:11.240 --> 01:06:15.598
-Sir, you have to understand...
-No, you have to understand.

1099
01:06:16.560 --> 01:06:20.349
The boys here aren't used
to the concepts you're bandying about.

1100
01:06:20.960 --> 01:06:23.349
The "M" word, Nicholas.

1101
01:06:23.440 --> 01:06:27.479
There hasn't been a recorded murder
in Sandford for 20 years.

1102
01:06:27.560 --> 01:06:29.312
But, sir, I'm certain.

1103
01:06:29.800 --> 01:06:32.918
And what's more, I know who did it.

1104
01:06:33.240 --> 01:06:38.235


1105
01:06:38.720 --> 01:06:40.552
Can I see the manager, please?

1106
01:06:45.840 --> 01:06:51.552
Mr Skinner to the Manager's office.
Manager's office. Mr Skinner.

1107
01:06:52.240 --> 01:06:55.551
Sergeant Angel.
And to what do I owe this pleasure?

1108
01:06:55.640 --> 01:06:59.554
Simon Skinner, I'm arresting you
on suspicion of the murder of Leslie Tiller.

1109
01:06:59.640 --> 01:07:02.951
Leslie Tiller's dead? How?

1110
01:07:03.080 --> 01:07:05.310
She tripped and fell on her own shears.

1111
01:07:05.400 --> 01:07:06.470
(GROANS)

1112
01:07:06.880 --> 01:07:10.077
I'm also arresting you on suspicion of
the murder of Tim Messenger on May 1st,

1113
01:07:10.160 --> 01:07:11.719
of George Merchant on April 29th

1114
01:07:11.800 --> 01:07:14.269
and of Eve Draper
and Martin Blower on April 28th.

1115
01:07:14.360 --> 01:07:18.194
-Why on earth would I do that, Sergeant?
-I'm glad you asked.

1116
01:07:19.880 --> 01:07:21.951
My suspicions were first aroused
when you appeared

1117
01:07:22.040 --> 01:07:24.714
at the scene of the Blower-Draper death,
on the outskirts of Sandford,

1118
01:07:24.800 --> 01:07:28.475
despite the fact you live and work
in the centre of the village.

1119
01:07:29.640 --> 01:07:33.793
I couldn't help but recall your comments
at the theatre on the previous evening.

1120
01:07:34.040 --> 01:07:36.873
When you not only indicated
an awareness of the couple's affair

1121
01:07:36.960 --> 01:07:38.871
but also inferred
that Eve's connections at the council

1122
01:07:38.960 --> 01:07:41.793
might make her privy
to important information.

1123
01:07:41.880 --> 01:07:44.076
You even spoke of "bashing her head in."

1124
01:07:44.160 --> 01:07:47.630
Perhaps hoping you might discover
the route of the proposed Sandford Bypass.

1125
01:07:47.720 --> 01:07:49.870
You were already suspicious
that George Merchant was buying up

1126
01:07:49.960 --> 01:07:52.156
a large area of land
on the outskirts of Sandford,

1127
01:07:52.240 --> 01:07:55.073
after an article Tim Messenger
wrote in the Sandford Citizen.

1128
01:07:55.160 --> 01:07:58.676
You see, the land Merchant was buying
had little value in of itself but,

1129
01:07:58.760 --> 01:08:02.515
if it became accessible by road,
it would be a prime location for say,

1130
01:08:02.880 --> 01:08:04.473
a retail park.

1131
01:08:04.560 --> 01:08:06.471
Consumed with concern for your business

1132
01:08:06.560 --> 01:08:08.517
and potential disloyalty
from fickle customers,

1133
01:08:08.600 --> 01:08:11.069
you yourself expressed a wish to behead.

1134
01:08:11.560 --> 01:08:14.120
You killed the competition in cold blood.

1135
01:08:14.200 --> 01:08:16.032
Staging the murders as accidents.

1136
01:08:16.120 --> 01:08:19.078
You used a vehicle removal truck
to stage the Blower-Draper death

1137
01:08:19.160 --> 01:08:20.992
and incinerated an old man
in his own house.

1138
01:08:21.080 --> 01:08:24.152
Covering your tracks with the judicial
application of bacon and beans.

1139
01:08:24.240 --> 01:08:27.073
However, there was a loose end.

1140
01:08:28.080 --> 01:08:29.479
Tim Messenger.

1141
01:08:29.560 --> 01:08:31.631
Splattered before he could share with me

1142
01:08:31.720 --> 01:08:34.553
what he told Leslie Tiller
that very afternoon.

1143
01:08:34.640 --> 01:08:37.359
The true value of her land.

1144
01:08:37.720 --> 01:08:40.519
Upon discovering she was about
to sell up to the developers,

1145
01:08:40.600 --> 01:08:43.319
you brutally murdered her
with her own shears.

1146
01:08:43.400 --> 01:08:47.951
And made good your escape utilising
your impressive skills as a fun runner.

1147
01:08:54.160 --> 01:08:57.790
Very entertaining. But I rather think
you've been watching too many films.

1148
01:08:57.880 --> 01:08:59.234
(CLEARS THROAT)

1149
01:08:59.320 --> 01:09:00.355
He hasn't.

1150
01:09:00.440 --> 01:09:04.035
Why would [ kill Leslie?
You clearly aren't aware that we're related.

1151
01:09:04.120 --> 01:09:06.589
Oh, but I am, "Cousin Sissy."

1152
01:09:08.040 --> 01:09:12.193
I'm afraid my nickname of Sissy
is only a revelation to yourself.

1153
01:09:12.480 --> 01:09:15.711
My teenage years studying ballet
are well known.

1154
01:09:15.800 --> 01:09:18.838
-Yeah, Sissy Skinner.
-What a Gaylord.

1155
01:09:18.920 --> 01:09:20.399
Thank you, Andrews.

1156
01:09:20.480 --> 01:09:23.711
Now, despite my comments
about "beheading” customers,

1157
01:09:23.800 --> 01:09:27.191
I personally relish the competition
of another store.

1158
01:09:27.280 --> 01:09:30.750
Anything to energise my workforce.

1159
01:09:32.200 --> 01:09:36.637
And anyway, what makes you think
I could dislodge part of the church roof?

1160
01:09:36.720 --> 01:09:39.075
Or for that matter, stage a car crash?

1161
01:09:39.160 --> 01:09:42.391
It's a well known fact that
the church roof is in dire need of repair.

1162
01:09:42.480 --> 01:09:44.551
And isn't it true
that two of your own employees

1163
01:09:44.640 --> 01:09:46.995
operate the vehicle removal service
for the council?

1164
01:09:47.080 --> 01:09:49.356
Sergeant, this is the 21st Century.

1165
01:09:49.440 --> 01:09:52.239
Many people hold down several jobs.

1166
01:09:52.320 --> 01:09:55.870
I myself host a life drawing class
at the Village Hall.

1167
01:09:55.960 --> 01:09:58.873
Tina here is a table dancer at Flappers.

1168
01:09:59.200 --> 01:10:02.909
Nevertheless, you could have utilised
the vehicle removal truck for your own ends.

1169
01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:04.957
These accusations
are quite meaningless, Sergeant,

1170
01:10:05.040 --> 01:10:07.554
unless you can back them up
with hard evidence.

1171
01:10:07.640 --> 01:10:10.109
Well, you've got me there.

1172
01:10:10.200 --> 01:10:12.111
I'd need something conclusive.

1173
01:10:12.200 --> 01:10:14.271
Something that placed you
at the scene of the crime.

1174
01:10:14.360 --> 01:10:18.240
Perhaps a wound you sustained on
a piece of broken glass this very evening.

1175
01:10:19.800 --> 01:10:21.393
This very evening.

1176
01:10:22.600 --> 01:10:25.752
Sergeant, this is beginning
to get embarrassing.

1177
01:10:25.840 --> 01:10:28.878
How could I possibly be
in several places at once?

1178
01:10:31.080 --> 01:10:35.551
I'm sure the store's security footage
will absolve me.

1179
01:10:36.240 --> 01:10:38.800
Do feel free to spool through.

1180
01:10:55.560 --> 01:10:56.595
I can handle this, Danny.

1181
01:10:56.680 --> 01:10:59.832
You might as well go back
and just enjoy the rest of your birthday.

1182
01:10:59.920 --> 01:11:02.389
-Did you really get me that plant?
-Yes, I did.

1183
01:11:02.480 --> 01:11:05.791
But it's been impounded as evidence.

1184
01:11:05.880 --> 01:11:10.317
Well, I mean,
maybe Dad will still let me water it, eh?

1185
01:11:10.400 --> 01:11:11.515
Yeah.

1186
01:11:14.800 --> 01:11:16.154
Sergeant, I wanted you to know that

1187
01:11:16.240 --> 01:11:19.437
if I do indeed now
own the land belonging to...

1188
01:11:21.120 --> 01:11:26.718
belonging to Leslie, that I intend to turn it
into a memorial garden, in her honour.

1189
01:11:26.800 --> 01:11:31.192
Mr Skinner, what you do with your land
is of no concern of mine,

1190
01:11:32.280 --> 01:11:33.793
(BLOWS RASPBERRY)

1191
01:11:33.880 --> 01:11:35.029
So jog on.

1192
01:11:35.880 --> 01:11:40.317
Michael, will you escort the Sergeant
off the premises when he's quite finished?

1193
01:11:40.400 --> 01:11:41.879
Yarp.

1194
01:11:44.880 --> 01:11:49.033
I just can't believe Leslie's dead.
How did it happen?

1195
01:11:49.120 --> 01:11:51.350
She tripped and fell on her own shears.

1196
01:11:59.160 --> 01:12:01.276
Hey, that weren't me.

1197
01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:10.115
Hey, look.

1198
01:12:10.200 --> 01:12:12.794
Look, Mr Treacher's
got his big coat on again.

1199
01:12:16.320 --> 01:12:20.553
-You want anything from the shop?
-Cornetto.

